Why is timely delivery crucial in software project management, and how can project managers ensure deadlines are met?
Timely delivery is important in SPM because software projects have tendencies of taking too long which leads to high human and capital resources, for a project manager to
ensure deadlines are met commuinication among teams is important and tasks should be broken down into acheievable timeframe

How does effective cost control contribute to the success of a software project? This helps keep a project to the confines of the allocated budget this helps when the need of project addition rises

What strategies can be used to prevent budget overruns? 
a strategy to prevent budget overuns is ensure proper planning process and means to ensure that all planned processes are  followed and communicated properly.


Compare and contrast Agile and Waterfall methodologies. What are the main advantages and disadvantages of each?

Agile methodology entails an iterative process while Waterfall methodology is more of a seqential process making planning detailed and done upfront.
The advantage of the Waterfall method is the strict deadline and budgets, plans and due diligence are carried out pre-project its disadvantage is the difficulty with making changes.
The advantage of the Agile method is the very flexible, it gives room for the customer's input and its disadavantage is the ever acceptance of change in design which most times can affect the budget

In what types of projects might Agile be more beneficial than Waterfall, and vice versa? Can you provide examples of each?
Agile is often preferred for projects with uncertain requirements or those that require rapid delivery, while Waterfall may be more suitable for projects with well-defined requirements and a fixed scope.
